        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 4:11AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 411 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Okemah, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Beggs...                          Preston...
Boley...                          Paden...
Weleetka...                       Dewar...
Clearview...                      Schulter...
Eram...                           Morris...
Pharoah...                        Grayson...
Bryant...                         Okmulgee...
Jamesville...                     Okemah...
Bald Hill...                      Okfuskee...
Henryetta...                      Mason...

This includes Interstate 40 in Oklahoma between mile markers 212 and
240.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for
southeastern, northeastern and east central Oklahoma.</instruction>
